The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Sati sons in murder net

 Bhopal, Sept. 21: Police today arrested the four sons of Kuriya Devi, the 95-year-old woman who had allegedly committed sati, on murder charges, reports our special correspondent. 

 Police said residents of Baniyani village in Chhatarpur district, 275 km from here, told them that the four had taken their mother, in full bridal gear, to their fathers pyre, which was lit by her youngest son. 

 Kuriya Devis four sons have been taken into custody for murder and under the Prevention of Sati Act, inspector-general of police Swarn Singh said. 




